al; the potential and recent form of the show jumping team; the possibility that one of the quartet of golfers could put themselves into contention; and more opportunities for the rowers tomorrow in the shapes of theFermanagh duo of Ross Corrigan and Nathan Timoney in the men's pair, Margaret Cremen and Aoife Casey in the women's lightweight double sculls, and of course, defending Olympic men's lightweight double sculls champions Paul O'Donovan and Fintan McCarthy, the sight of the tricolour being hoisted a few more times looks likely.\", \"from\": 2282, \"to\": 2909, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2312, \"end\": 2328, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rhys_McClenaghan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rhys McClenaghan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rhys_McClenaghan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rhys_McClenaghan\"}, {\"begin\": 2601, \"end\": 2605, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ross_Geller\", \"score\": 0.9999999999881766, \"rank\": 1.1900403719388494e-11, \"text\": \"Ross\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ross_Geller\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ross_Geller\"}, {\"begin\": 2619, \"end\": 2625, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nathan_Petrelli\", \"score\": 0.9999997955415192, \"rank\": 1.4964259562510642e-07, \"text\": \"Nathan\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nathan_Petrelli\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nathan_Petrelli\"}, {\"begin\": 2626, \"end\": 2633, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Timoney_Technology_Limited_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Timoney\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Timoney_Technology_Limited_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Timoney_Technology_Limited_of_Ireland\"}, {\"begin\"